{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Alter the Union Flag to include something that represents Wales",
        "additional_details": "At the time of the creation of the first Union Flag in 1606, Wales was considered a Principality of England. But things have moved on:\r\n- Since 1948, many laws passed in Parliament are designated as applicable to \"England and Wales\".\r\n- In 1998 the National Assembly for Wales was established.\r\n- In 2011 Wales was recognised as a separate country by the International Standards Association.\r\n\r\nThe Union Flag should be a symbol of all of Great Britain.  Any objections to that would be deeply unpatriotic.",
        "background": "The Union Flag does not contain any symbol representing Wales.  To symbolise our Great Union we should produce an updated flag which does.",
